{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> ἐργᾰσ-ία</b>, <br /> <i>Ionic dialect</i> -ιη, Cretan dialect <b>ϝεργασία</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"“Leg.Gort.” 8.44, ἡ, (ἐργάτης)\">Refs</a>] <b>work, business,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" ἐργασίην φεύγουσα “hymnus ad Mercurium” 486 \">Refs</a>], etc.; opposed to ἀργία, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Mem.” 2.7.7; ἐ. ἀγαθή\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] productive <b>labour,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev\\. author] “Vect.” 4.29; ἐργασίᾳ ἐγχειρεῖν, of bees, 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “HA” 625b24; ἡ περὶ τὴν θάλατταν ἐ., of seamen, 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “R.” 371b; μὴ γενομένης ἐργασίας\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] if no <b>work</b> was done, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 27.20; δὸς ἐργασίαν,\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>] with <i>infinitive</i>, Latin <i>da operam ut..,</i> NT.Luke.12.58, compare [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"“OGI” 441.109 (_SC. de Stratonicensibus,_ 1st c.BC): _plural_, τὰς ἐν ὑπαίθρῳ ἐ. ἐργάζεσθαι Xenophon Historicus [{5-6th c.BC}] “Oeconomicus” 7.20; ἐ. ἀνελεύθεροι 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Ethica Nicomachea” 1121b33, compare 4th-3rd c.BC: Epicurus Philosophus “fragment” 196 (uncertain). \">Refs 6th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> <b>function,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" ἥπατος 2nd c.AD: Aretaeus Medicus “περὶ αἰτιῶν καὶ σημείων χρονίων παθῶν” 1.15 \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]. <br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <b>working at, making, manufacture,</b> ἱματίων, ὑποδημάτων, etc., [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Grg.” 449d, “Tht.” 146d, etc.; ἡ τῆς ἐσθῆτος ἐκ τῶν ἐρίων ἐ. Xenophon Historicus [{5-6th c.BC}] “Oeconomicus” 7.21 \">Refs 6th c.BC+</a>]; <b>making up</b> of a prescription, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus “Ulc.” 14: _metaphorically_, Πέργαμος ἀμφὶ τεαῖς χερὸς ἐργασίαις ἁλίσκεται Troy is (i.e. is doomed to be)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] taken in the part <b>wrought by</b> thy <b>hands,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “O.” 8.42; ἐ. ἡδονῆς\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] <b>production</b> of pleasure, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Prt.” 353d; ἐ. χρημάτων\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] money-<b>making,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “EN” 1160a16 (but _administration_ of property, “Leg.Gort.” [same place]). \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.2</b></Level3> <b>working</b> of a material, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" ἡ ἐ. τοῦ σιδήρου 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 1.68 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; χαλκοῦ, ἐρίων, ξύλων, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Chrm.” 173e; τῶν χρυσείων μετάλλων 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 4.105, compare 4th c.BC: Hyperides Orator “Eux.” 36; πίττης Theophrastus Philosophus [{4-3rd c.BC}] “Historia Plantarum” 9.2.6 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: most commonly, <b>tillage</b> of the ground, ἐ. γῆς, χώρας, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Ra.” 1034 (_plural_), 5th-6th c.BC: Isocrates Orator 7.30, etc.; ἐ. κήπων Plato Philosophus [{5-6th c.BC}] “Minos” 316b \">Refs 6th c.BC+</a>]; ἐ. περὶ τὴν τροφήν <b>preparation</b> (i.e. mastication and digestion) of food, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Juv.” 469a3 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; <b>treatment</b> of silphium, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-3rd c.BC: Theophrastus Philosophus “HP” 6.3.2 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.3</b></Level3> generally, <b>trade, business,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Mem.” 3.10.1; ἐπὶ τῆς ἐργασίας ὢν τῆς κατὰ θάλατταν\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] engaged in <b>trade</b> by sea, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 33.4; ἡ ἐ. τῆς τραπέζης\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>] the banking <b>business,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev\\. author] 36.6; ἐ. χρυσοχοϊκή, ἀρωματική, “PLond.” 3.906.6 (2nd c.AD), “PFay.” 93.7 (2nd c.AD); βαφεῖς τὴν ἐ.\">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>] dyers by <b>trade,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" PTeb. 287.3(2nd c.AD)\">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]; especially of <b>a courtesan's trade,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 2.135, 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 18.129 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; of sexual <b>intercourse,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Pr.” 876a39. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level4><b>__II.3.b</b></Level4> ἐὰν ἐργασίαν εὕρῃ ὁ οἰκέτης if a slave brings in <b>earnings,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Hyperides Orator “Ath.” 22. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.4</b></Level3> <b>practising, exercising,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" τῶν τεχνῶν Plato Philosophus [{5-6th c.BC}] “Gorgias” 450c; Κύπριδος “AP” 5.218 (Paul. Sil.); ἀκαθαρσίας “Epistle to the Ephesians” 4.19 \">Refs 6th c.BC+</a>]. <br /><Level3><b>__II.5</b></Level3> <b>work of art, production,</b> τετράγωνος ἐ., of the Hermae, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 6.27 (non legit Scholia); τῶν τειχῶν αἱ ἐργασίαι\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] the fortification <b>works,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev\\. author] 7.6. \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.6</b></Level3> literary <b>execution,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" ἐ. ποιητική 1st c.BC: Philodemus Philosophus “περὶ ποιημάτων” 5.11 \">Refs 1st c.BC+</a>]; <b>elaboration</b> of a topic, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"Scholia 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “P.” 2.24. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.7</b></Level3> <b>production</b> of a play, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" Arg. 4th-3rd c.BC: Menander Comicus “Oxy.” 1235.108. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__III</b></Level2> <b>guild</b> or <b>company</b> of workmen, ἡ ἐ. τῶν βαφέων[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" Judeich “Altertümer von Hierapolis” 50 \">Refs</a>]; ἐριοπλυτῶν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"[prev. work] 40; ἐ. θρεμματική uncertain meaning, [prev. work]227. \">Refs</a>]","strongNumber":"G2039","accentedUnicode":"ἐργασία","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G2038","matchingForm":"ἐργάζομαι","stepTransliteration":"ergazomai","gloss":"to work","_zh_tw_Gloss":"作工, 作, 行","_es_Gloss":"trabajar","_zh_Gloss":"作工, 作, 行"},{"strongNumber":"G2040","matchingForm":"ἐργάτης","stepTransliteration":"ergatēs","gloss":"worker","_zh_tw_Gloss":"工人","_es_Gloss":"obrero","_zh_Gloss":"工人"},{"strongNumber":"G2041","matchingForm":"ἔργον","stepTransliteration":"ergon","gloss":"work","_zh_tw_Gloss":"行為, 工作, 事","_es_Gloss":"obra","_zh_Gloss":"行为, 工作, 事"},{"strongNumber":"G2110","matchingForm":"εὐεργέτης","stepTransliteration":"euergetēs","gloss":"benefactor","_zh_tw_Gloss":"恩主","_es_Gloss":"benefactor","_zh_Gloss":"恩主"},{"strongNumber":"G2716","matchingForm":"κατεργάζομαι","stepTransliteration":"katergazomai","gloss":"to workout/produce","_zh_tw_Gloss":"行, 作","_es_Gloss":"llevar a cabo/producir","_zh_Gloss":"行, 作"},{"strongNumber":"G4020","matchingForm":"περιεργάζομαι","stepTransliteration":"periergazomai","gloss":"be a busybody","_zh_tw_Gloss":"好管閒事","_es_Gloss":"ser un entrometido","_zh_Gloss":"好管闲事"},{"strongNumber":"G4021","matchingForm":"περίεργος","stepTransliteration":"periergos","gloss":"meddlesome/magic","_zh_tw_Gloss":"邪術, 好管閑事","_es_Gloss":"entrometido/magia","_zh_Gloss":"邪术, 好管闲事"},{"strongNumber":"G4333","matchingForm":"προσεργάζομαι","stepTransliteration":"prosergazomai","gloss":"to earn more","_zh_tw_Gloss":"已經賺了","_es_Gloss":"ganar más","_zh_Gloss":"已经赚了"},{"strongNumber":"G4903","matchingForm":"συνεργέω","stepTransliteration":"sunergeō","gloss":"to work with","_zh_tw_Gloss":"同工","_es_Gloss":"trabajar con","_zh_Gloss":"同工"},{"strongNumber":"G4904","matchingForm":"συνεργός","stepTransliteration":"sunergos","gloss":"co-worker","_zh_tw_Gloss":"同工","_es_Gloss":"colaborador","_zh_Gloss":"同工"}],"shortDef":"trade, business, making money; indulgence","mediumDef":"trade, business, making money; indulgence <br /><b>work, labor;</b>, in NT <greek>ἐργασιαν διδόναι</greek>, <b>to endeavor, strive,</b> <ref='Luk.12.58'>Lk. 12:58</ref>; <b>performance, practice,</b> <ref='Eph.4.19'>Eph. 4:19;</ref> <b>a trade, business, craft,</b> <ref='Act.19.25'>Acts 19:25</ref>, <b>gain</b> acquired by labor or trade, <b>profit,</b> <ref='Act.16.16, 19; 19.24'>Acts 16:16, 19; 19:24</ref>*","stepGloss":"work","stepTransliteration":"ergasia","count":6,"_es_Definition":"ganancia, ventaja ; negocio; práctica ; procurar (LUC.12:58)","_zh_tw_Definition":"1) 追逐, 奉行 (弗 4:19)<br>2) 生意, 買賣 (徒 19:25)<br>3) 獲利, 利潤<br>4) 盡力, 嘔心瀝血 (路 12:58)","_zh_Definition":"1) 追逐, 奉行 (弗 4:19)<br>2) 生意, 买卖 (徒 19:25)<br>3) 获利, 利润<br>4) 尽力, 呕心沥血 (路 12:58)","_step_Type":"word","_vi_Definition":"lợi lộc; việc làm; hoạt động. Xem G2040/2041","_zh_tw_Gloss":"生意","_es_Gloss":"obra","_zh_Gloss":"生意"}]}